 The Labour Court has reserved judgment in Nehawus appeal of the interdict. It will only hand down its decision on Monday. In the meantime, the health union is forging ahead with the strike. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu reports. #dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Nehawu members will know next week whether they're allowed to continue with their strike or have to call it off. Judgment on the union's appeal of an interdict preventing the strike will be handed down on Monday. READ: President slams Nehawu protest In the meantime, the health workers are forging ahead with their protest action. They're not budging from their demand of a 10 percent wage increase and say the 4,7 percent offered by government is an insult. * eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu reports.